    "The readout signal in each shot of the experiment is compared with a preset threshold that lies between the two levels, as we see in the readout histograms in Fig. 2b.",
    "We assign value 1 to a blockaded readout, and value 0 to an unblockaded readout.",
    "Finally, we average over all shots to obtain P blockade for the statistics.",
    "Extended Data Fig. 2f shows the ESR spectrum as a function of V J, in which we identify two regimes.",
    "At V J < 1.175 V, only two transitions pertaining to the driven rotation of the individual qubits are detected."
